GoogleSearchSnippets is a component which can be used in order to extract the snippets from Google's search engine.

By only setting the term that you want to search for and the number of results you want to get. 

You can use this component by only importing into your code the following line:
JavaGoogleSearch jgs = new JavaGoogleSearch("term", 50); 
where the first parameter is a String and the second one an integer.

There is also the capability of extracting these snippets into a XML format, such as following:

<docID>
	<title>
		Russel - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
	</title>
	<body>
		en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russel - Cached - SimilarRussel. From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia. Jump to: navigation, search.   Russel is an alternate 			spelling of Russell. Russel may refer to: ...
	</body>
	<address>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russel&amp;sa=U&amp;ei=AAExUL2cL6eQ0AWNjYDoDA&amp;ved=0CBMQFjAA&amp;usg=AFQjCNGzMEtbjEetCj6OYO7pq9Z__aGrHA</address>
</docID> 


